1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:11,500
<i> Aren't you coming home yet?</i>

2
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,367
<i> Not yet.</i>

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,133
<i> When?</i>

4
00:00:13,267 --> 00:00:15,733
<i> Do what we agreed on first.</i>

5
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:16,800
<i> I'm sorry,</i>

6
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:19,500
<i>but you have to come home first,
Manuel.</i>

7
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> The nerve of her!</i>

8
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,700
<i>What if she doesn't keep
her side of the bargain?</i>

9
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,100
<i> I won't let her do that again.</i>

10
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:27,800
<i>I might end up killing her
myself.</i>

11
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,433
<i> I knew it. They're here.</i>

12
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:32,800
<i>Mom, why are you packing
Dad's stuff?</i>

13
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:37,367
<i>Your mom and I decided
we'd go on a trip.</i>

14
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:39,533
<i>We're just here to enjoy, okay?</i>

15
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:42,767
<i>Your mom and I want us all
to be happy.</i>

16
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,200
<i> While I'm still here.</i>

17
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> Dad...</i>

18
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:56,333
So, they went missing
during the shift.

19
00:00:56,467 --> 00:00:58,233
Miles caught them.

20
00:00:58,367 --> 00:00:59,733
As in Miles herself.

21
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:01,333
They were caught smoking
on the rooftop.

22
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:03,000
They got suspended.

23
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:07,033
Friend.

24
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,667
I've been sharing the latest
news in Southcrest

25
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:11,967
with you for a while.

26
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,167
I can't reach Felma and Manuel.

27
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,400
That's what I'm talking about.

28
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,167
That's what you get
for acting hard to get.

29
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:22,367
Now you're panicking,
wanting to call them.

30
00:01:24,867 --> 00:01:26,133
Darn them.

31
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:30,867
Alice, what if they ran away
from me?

32
00:01:33,067 --> 00:01:34,800
Instead of coming back to you,

33
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:38,167
Manuel might have gone far away
with his family.

34
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:40,733
They took Coleen away
and hid her.

35
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:55,600
Let's go, darling.

36
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:56,967
There they are.

37
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:57,700
Wait.

38
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,600
Take a picture first.

39
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:01,400
With that in the background.

40
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:02,200
Come here.

41
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:02,900
Where?

42
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,200
- There, there.
- There!

43
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,733
Nice.

44
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:11,533
One more, darling.

45
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:13,200
Give me your big,
wonderful smile.

46
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,233
There.

47
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,933
Wait.

48
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:18,500
Why is Hazel calling?

49
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:19,233
What?

50
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:24,367
Darling, more pictures!

51
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,333
There.

52
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,433
There you go.

53
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:32,267
- Hazel's pestering me!
- What?

54
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,433
Give me that.

55
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:44,867
Why are you calling her?

56
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,167
Abel.

57
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,700
Hey, witch!

58
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,467
What do you need
from my husband?

59
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,267
Is Manuel with you?

60
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,633
Yes, yes, yes.

61
00:02:59,767 --> 00:03:00,633
Let me talk to him.

62
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:03,000
No, no, no!

63
00:03:03,133 --> 00:03:04,200
What do you mean by no?

64
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:05,833
Give him the phone.

65
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:07,700
Sorry, girl.

66
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:11,900
Do not disturb him.
He's with his real family.

67
00:03:12,033 --> 00:03:13,033
And excuse me.

68
00:03:13,167 --> 00:03:14,467
Do you think you can order me
around?

69
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,333
You're not my boss!

70
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,333
Hold on.

71
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,600
Darling!

72
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,933
I said I can manage.

73
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:26,267
JB, be careful around Didang.

74
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,267
She's a real guard-snatcher
in our village.

75
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:31,267
- Jeff! What are you saying.
- Those are your rivals.

76
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,700
Don't believe him.

77
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:36,667
Auntie!

78
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,267
Say hello!

79
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,633
Hi!

80
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,867
With my baby!

81
00:03:44,733 --> 00:03:46,000
Stop bothering us.

82
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:49,067
Go find someone else
to mess with.

83
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,100
- Okay? Thanks, bye!
- Paz!

84
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:52,667
Paz.

85
00:03:58,067 --> 00:04:04,133
Auntie!

86
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:06,067
They still had the nerve
to celebrate!

87
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,933
They're celebrating, Alice!

88
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,733
They're monsters!

89
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:13,133
Where the hell are they?

90
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:15,533
They're in Matawhay Resort.

91
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:17,867
How did you know?

92
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,200
All you could think about
is anger.

93
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:24,100
That's why you didn't notice it.

94
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,233
Right?

95
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:31,167
Here are the two deluxe rooms.

96
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:34,167
And the couple's room
is at the front.

97
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:34,967
Okay.

98
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:37,533
Girls will stay in Room 103.

99
00:04:37,667 --> 00:04:40,133
Wait. Hold on, Ma'am.

100
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:43,967
I'd better check it first.
Stay here for now. Just wait.

101
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,667
Didang?

102
00:04:58,167 --> 00:04:59,000
Clear.

103
00:04:59,133 --> 00:04:59,900
Safe.

104
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,333
It's okay.

105
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:04,933
It's safe.

106
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:06,633
The other one. Hurry!

107
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:08,367
Open it, open it.

108
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:17,333
You know what, Didang?

109
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:18,900
You're just trying to get JB's
attention.

110
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:22,333
Quit it already.

111
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,067
Come on.

112
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,700
Shut up, Jeff.

113
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:30,967
I'm checking for evil spirits
and elements here,

114
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:33,000
hanging out in the room.

115
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,067
Safe.

116
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,967
Didang, did you feel anything?

117
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,100
Nothing.

118
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:42,700
Just like the other room,
it's safe.

119
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,467
But you're asking if I feel
anything? Yes.

120
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,700
I feel something. A spirit.

121
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,633
Like a soulmate.

122
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:53,267
It seems that my soulmate
is here.

123
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:56,367
You're driving me nuts, Didang!

124
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,867
So you were just flirting,
and you're using us.

125
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,667
What a waste of time.
You're insane!

126
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,933
JB, let's go.

127
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:07,733
Come with my husband and me.
Show us our room.

128
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,967
Ma'am, I'm serious!

129
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:14,567
I'll check your room first.
To make sure there's no bad...

130
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,300
Didang, let's go.

131
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:17,433
Let's go inside the room.

132
00:06:17,567 --> 00:06:21,267
- i'll check.
- Quit it. That's enough.

133
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,200
Go inside.

134
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,133
Stop.

135
00:06:27,567 --> 00:06:28,633
Let's go, Alice.

136
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:32,067
Where are we going?
Wait, I'm still on duty.

137
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,400
We're going to Manuel.

138
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:34,700
We'll go to the resort.

139
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,700
Search the web for the exact
address.

140
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:37,700
Are you serious?

141
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:38,833
Yes!

142
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:39,833
Wait.

143
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,900
We'll join their family bonding.

144
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:44,833
I'm the real wife.
I should be there.

145
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:46,767
Hazel, wait! Friend!

146
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:53,567
It's so good.
There's a lot of crab fat.

147
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,767
Dad, we'll do that.

148
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,567
Yes, Dad. We got it.

149
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,067
No, it's okay. I got this.

150
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,433
Let me serve you.

151
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:01,867
You were still kids

152
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,900
the last time I peeled shrimps
for you.

153
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:12,033
The night before you left for...

154
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:14,733
Was it the last time?

155
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,267
Wow, you still remember it.

156
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,067
You're good at it, Dad.

157
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:23,600
- You peel it so fast.
- Of course, I'm an expert.

158
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:25,533
Is it the first time
you've seen it?

159
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:26,467
Oh, yeah.

160
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,967
She doesn't know
the story behind it.

161
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,033
Bro, tell them what happened

162
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:32,100
when Felma's having pregnancy
cravings.

163
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:33,267
Oh, yeah.

164
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:37,500
When your mom was pregnant
with Jeffrey,

165
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:40,133
she didn't eat anything
but shrimp.

166
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:45,933
She ate one kilo of shrimp
every day for two months.

167
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:47,700
Every day, Mom?

168
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:48,833
That's true.

169
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:51,967
And your mom was being cutesy.

170
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,533
Your dad kept peeling shrimps,
and she was eating everything.

171
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:59,000
Out of all the shrimp your dad
peeled over two months,

172
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:02,167
he didn't eat a single one.

173
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,167
Your mom ate them all.

174
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:06,000
Every day, Mom?

175
00:08:08,067 --> 00:08:11,000
Mom's being sentimental.

176
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,633
No, I just remember.

177
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:19,933
I only realized later
that your dad barely slept.

178
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:25,867
After driving the tricycle,
when I was already asleep,

179
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:30,233
he'd go out to sell balut.

180
00:08:30,367 --> 00:08:32,733
Every night, he worked extra

181
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:36,767
just to make sure he could buy
me shrimp every day.

182
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:41,967
So sweet!

183
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,500
Did you really do that, Manuel?

184
00:08:43,633 --> 00:08:46,367
Wow. I didn't know that.

185
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,800
You really love my friend.

186
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:53,000
Meanwhile,

187
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:56,500
when I was craving suman
while pregnant with Mayette,

188
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,800
someone didn't even bother
buying me any!

189
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:02,100
Suman? Just suman, darling?

190
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:06,067
Just so that Felma, Manuel,
and all of you know,

191
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:09,400
that suman she wanted
was from Alaminos.

192
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:11,500
Was I supposed to go
to Pangasinan every day

193
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:14,033
just to get you suman?

194
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:20,733
Wow! That's too much!

195
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:24,967
After this, let's go swimming.
I want to go swimming.

196
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,733
Right.

197
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:29,900
And karaoke!

198
00:09:30,067 --> 00:09:31,067
Didang!

199
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,867
And let's have a bonfire later
tonight.

200
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:37,367
We'll do all of that, kids.

201
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:41,233
We'll create memories
you'll never forget.

202
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:44,133
Yeah. So starting now,
we'll capture everything.

203
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,733
Picture! Picture!

204
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:53,600
One, two...

205
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:58,933
Closer, closer.
Picture.

206
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:08,067
Mr. Handsome is here!

207
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,167
This is my chance.

208
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,600
It's still fresh.

209
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:22,667
Mr. Handsome.

210
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,267
It shouldn't be obvious,
so he can catch me.

211
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,900
I'm feeling dizzy.

212
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:40,767
I'm full.

213
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:42,367
I want to go swimming.

214
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:45,100
- Can we go now?
- Yes!

215
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:45,900
Game!

216
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:47,500
Let's race!

217
00:10:48,767 --> 00:10:51,567
Hey, wait! You've just eaten!

218
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,300
Wait, sis.

219
00:10:53,433 --> 00:10:55,067
Why are you going to hit your
children with your slipper?

220
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,100
Oh, yeah.

221
00:10:56,233 --> 00:10:58,933
Sorry, I forgot that
they're no longer kids.

222
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:03,033
Sis.

223
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:05,933
Abel and I will just take
a walk.

224
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,500
Sure. Go on.

225
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:15,167
Baby time?

226
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,633
Abel's so silly.

227
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,333
Felma, are you okay?

228
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:22,933
My head suddenly hurts.

229
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:24,867
Let's go to the clinic.
Let's ask for medicine.

230
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,033
Come on.

231
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:27,333
No need.

232
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,333
This will eventually go away.

233
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,700
Let's go to the kids.

234
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,733
Good afternoon.

235
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:47,800
Give me that.

236
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:51,300
Hello! Welcome to Matawhay
Garden Resorts.

237
00:11:51,433 --> 00:11:52,700
Such a lovely place.

238
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:54,467
- Such a lovely.
- Enough with the intro.

239
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,567
We don't have a reservation,
but I need a room.

240
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,900
- Is there any available?
- Yes, Ma'am.

241
00:11:58,033 --> 00:12:01,033
We have a villa, a deluxe room,
and a couple's room.

242
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:02,700
As long as the two of us fit.
I'll get it.

243
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:04,300
I'll check for a while, Ma'am.

244
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:06,633
I'll give you complimentary
drinks for now.

245
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,600
No illegitimate family is going
to enjoy today.

246
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:16,000
Because I'm going
to ruin their day.

247
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:18,967
Why did you make us wait
for so long?

248
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:20,900
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

249
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:22,700
We had to clean
the room first.

250
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,300
You cleaned it that long?

251
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:26,967
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

252
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:27,933
This way, please.

253
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,733
I'm hungry.
Let's order some food first.

254
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,633
- How can we order?
- Let's go.

255
00:12:32,767 --> 00:12:34,000
We still don't have a room.

256
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:36,733
We need to see the room first.

257
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:46,033
Hi, JB.

258
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:48,100
Do you need anything, Ma'am?

259
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:53,867
I have a lot to ask you.

260
00:12:55,133 --> 00:13:00,033
Maybe you can help me.

261
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:02,133
They're asking
for too much.

262
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:04,000
Maybe you can.

263
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:09,633
Ma'am!

264
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:16,167
Ma'am, are you okay?

265
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:25,100
<i> It's annoying.</i>

266
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,200
Hazel?

267
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,667
Oh, no.

268
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:39,700
I know we were brought together,
but I'm not sure it was fate.

269
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:41,400
I don't want to hurt you.

270
00:13:41,767 --> 00:13:43,267
So, bye!

271
00:13:46,933 --> 00:13:48,667
That's too far!

272
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:58,500
Darling, let's go back
to our room.

273
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:01,300
I'm tired from walking.

274
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:03,300
We only stayed at the fountain.

275
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:05,400
You just started walking,
and you're already tired?

276
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,167
Baby time?

277
00:14:13,767 --> 00:14:15,333
Let's go. Hurry.

278
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,667
- Ouch!
-The keys. Hey!

279
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,833
Didang, what's going on
with you?

280
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:23,667
Let's play a game.

281
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,067
- Okay.
- Let's find this one peso coin.

282
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,767
Don't think I'm cheating.

283
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:30,267
Hey, you have trust issues!

284
00:14:30,433 --> 00:14:33,100
Whoever finds this will get
five hundred pesos from Dad.

285
00:14:33,233 --> 00:14:35,800
- Promise, Dad?
- Five hundred.

286
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:38,100
- Wait! Wait!
- Wow!

287
00:14:39,933 --> 00:14:42,200
- One, two, three.
- Go!

288
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:49,133
It's the first time
I've seen them like that.

289
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:51,667
That happy.
Like kids having fun.

290
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:55,933
You're lucky you still get
to see them like that.

291
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:59,633
For me, this is the last time.

292
00:14:59,767 --> 00:15:01,667
Manuel, don't say that.

293
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,667
Weren't you the one who told us
earlier not to be sad?

294
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,300
We're supposed to be happy.

295
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:10,067
Did you find it?

296
00:15:11,367 --> 00:15:14,067
- Who found it?
- Who?

297
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:14,967
Got it!

298
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,767
- Andeng is good!
- I don't think she dived.

299
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,033
She didn't dive.

300
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,933
It seemed you just got another
coin.

301
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:28,900
Dad, we'll just share the prize.

302
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:30,233
We'll get wet.

303
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,167
- You guys are being a handful.
- Dad, five hundred.

304
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:43,233
Why me?

305
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:44,600
We'll share it.

306
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:45,400
Ask your mom.

307
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:46,300
I'll get a thousand.

308
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,100
Dad, let's go swimming.

309
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:51,100
Go on. We'll just watch you.

310
00:15:51,233 --> 00:15:55,300
- Yeah. Go ahead and swim.
- Go on. Go.

311
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:58,433
Dad, how's your therapy?

312
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:02,200
Dad has started hydrotherapy.

313
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:03,067
Right?

314
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,100
Yes.

315
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:08,667
Doctor Tamayo said
I'm making fast progress.

316
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,600
But of course,

317
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:14,433
there's no guarantee
I'll be able to walk again.

318
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,800
But is there a chance, Dad?

319
00:16:16,933 --> 00:16:19,067
Of course, dear.

320
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:23,033
Remember, while there's life,
there's hope.

321
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:26,933
Dad, bring me along to your next
therapy session.

322
00:16:27,067 --> 00:16:28,333
You're always bringing Jeff
along.

323
00:16:28,467 --> 00:16:30,767
You're so envious.

324
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,800
Your bangs are scattered.

325
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:34,200
Mom!

326
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,500
- You two...
- I'll take a picture of you.

327
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:36,567
One happy.

328
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,833
Happy what?

329
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:40,867
- One happy family!
- Picture! Okay!

330
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:48,900
One, two...

331
00:16:52,367 --> 00:16:56,133
- Dad, come on!
- No, we're okay here.

332
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:04,567
- We can't get wet. Come on.
- We might get a spasm.

333
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:08,767
I'll just get some snacks.

334
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:13,267
I'm sure they'll get hungry once
they get out of the pool.

335
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,300
Look.

336
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:16,533
Pool fight.

337
00:17:16,667 --> 00:17:17,767
How do you do that?

338
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,033
It doesn't seem fun.

339
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:20,833
- No. Come on.
- Win?

340
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,767
- You might hurt each other!
- Be careful!

341
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:39,167
- I'll be right back. Careful!
- Hey, be careful!

342
00:17:41,367 --> 00:17:43,267
You saw something.

343
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,367
- What's that? English? Tagalog?
- Dancing? You saw something.

344
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,433
Is it a place?

345
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,667
Food!

346
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,400
Horns.

347
00:17:50,533 --> 00:17:51,333
- Horns.
- What's that?

348
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,533
- Carabao?
- Goat?

349
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:55,633
A bad spirit came.

350
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:56,733
It's Hazel.

351
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:57,767
What?

352
00:17:57,900 --> 00:17:59,567
Hazel's here?

353
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,300
Yes.

354
00:18:01,433 --> 00:18:02,733
Hazel's here?

355
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:05,933
Yes, Ma'am.

356
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:09,800
Hey, be careful!

357
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:23,400
Miss, over there.

358
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:25,467
Excuse me.

359
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,767
- Please move.
- Be careful.

360
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,767
- Okay.
- There.

361
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:35,567
Where's Mom?

362
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:39,667
She probably wandered around.

363
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,733
Got bored waiting for us.

364
00:18:41,867 --> 00:18:44,300
That's what I was telling you.
You took so long.

365
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,267
You took pictures
like it's forever.

366
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,433
Hey, didn't you join us?

367
00:18:50,133 --> 00:18:52,767
Before that becomes an issue,
let's set up everything

368
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:55,633
so we can start the party
as soon as Mom arrives.

369
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,267
- Right, Dad?
- Okay, okay. Move, move.

370
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:00,467
Joel, take a lot of pictures.
And then send them to me.

371
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,800
Okay, let's go.

372
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:04,500
I'll transfer it right away
once we get home.

373
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:09,267
- Okay, picture.
- Here.

374
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,400
One, two, three. One more.

375
00:19:11,533 --> 00:19:13,867
One, two, three.

376
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:16,767
They'd better be ready for me.

377
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,833
Friend, can we do that later?

378
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:20,700
I'm really starving.

379
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:22,967
Let's order food.

380
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,033
Fine.

381
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:27,467
I'll let them enjoy for now.

382
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,367
Even if I have all the right
to ruin their fun.

383
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:32,867
Go on.
Just order from room service.

384
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:39,167
Ma'am.

385
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:45,167
Who's that?

386
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:47,767
Someone's knocking so hard.

387
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:48,767
Who is this?

388
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:56,600
Hazel.

389
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:06,800
Alice, get out.

390
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,167
No!

391
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:12,267
Are you planning to gang up
on Hazel?

392
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,733
She's already at a disadvantage.

393
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:15,600
There are only the two of us,
and there are four of you.

394
00:20:17,033 --> 00:20:20,233
- I said get out!
- Ouch!

395
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,233
Felma, open the door!

396
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:32,967
- What are you doing?
- It hurts! Ouch!

397
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,333
- You!
- Ouch!

398
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:42,400
Hi!

399
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,067
Stay out of it.

400
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:52,700
So,

401
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:55,900
what do we do now, Felma?

402
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:57,567
Is this the part where...

403
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,833
we'll slap each other?
Pull each other's hair out?

404
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,033
No.

405
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:05,800
Are you scared?

406
00:21:05,933 --> 00:21:07,933
Don't be delusional.

407
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:10,500
Am I scared?

408
00:21:10,633 --> 00:21:15,433
Yes, because I might not be able
to hold myself back

409
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:17,500
and really go at you.

410
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:19,800
This is far from the hospital.

411
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:23,000
Don't flatter yourself too much.

412
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:25,367
So what,

413
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:29,167
are we going to play Rock,
Paper, Scissors for Manuel?

414
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,800
Stop being cheap, Hazel.

415
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:15,333
We already talked like educated
people.

416
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:18,033
What are you talking about,
Felma?

417
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:21,600
Between us, I'm the only
one who got a diploma.

418
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:24,667
Oh, yeah.

419
00:22:26,233 --> 00:22:27,533
I didn't finish school.

420
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,000
Unlike you.

421
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,433
But why does it seem...

422
00:22:37,767 --> 00:22:40,300
I'm more educated than you?

423
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:44,300
That's not how an educated
person behaves, right?

424
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:48,900
Seducing someone,
trapping someone into marriage,

425
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:53,167
and above all,
chasing after a man.

426
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:54,700
How dare you!

427
00:23:02,133 --> 00:23:03,267
Don't be stubborn.

428
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,233
And love your siblings.

429
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:06,533
I will.

430
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:11,100
I will serve him until he sees
that I'm deserving of love.

431
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:12,700
Don't make your hopes up.

432
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:14,800
I'm the one he loves.

433
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:17,000
Now that Noah is back,

434
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:20,200
maybe you can continue
your bond with him.

435
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,633
Keep treating him like your
father.

436
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,200
Maybe you're the one he loves.

437
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:28,300
But I'm still the one
and only real Mrs. Cruz.

438
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:30,567
Take care of them.

439
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,767
And take care of yourself.

440
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:36,733
Your name may be written
on paper as his wife,

441
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:41,367
but in Manuel's heart,
it's my name that's engraved.
